								<div class="title" id="post-title-3854378">
																		I want to like this but I cannot.
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mister-quillan" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1493231); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1493231&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610225122" alt="Mister Quillan" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1493231)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mister-quillan" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1493231); return false;" >Mister Quillan</a></span> <span class="odate time_1530241725 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 Jun 2018 03:08</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3854378">
									

<p>The concepts here are both fascinating and horrifying which seems appropriate for a doomsday article but the foundation, at least to me feels extremely out of character and surprisingly inept.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;lengthy&nbsp;explanation?&nbsp;</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide&nbsp;whatever</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I mean doesn't the foundation have access to many pocket universes that would be unaffected by this sort of phenomenon and various means to clone humans and lifeforms to sustain humans? It seemed clear to me reading this that whatever ''prime universe'' or at least planet earth in the said universe is inevitably doomed.</p>
<p>So I fail to understand why anyone here{in this foundation} is not focusing on some sort of evacuation of prime earth I mean if this worm thing destroys or damages or completely reconfigures that dimension wouldn't it stop after destroying its target? leaving the foundation in a position to rebuild as in something like ''recovered from the marinas trench'' especially if they could convince other G.O.Is to work with them given the dire circumstances.</p>
<p>It just doesn't seem very utilitarian to destroy countless dimensions to save one and I've always viewed the foundation as well-intentioned extremist utilitarians and the moral arithmetic does not add up. None of this comes across as for the greater good to me.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Of course, maybe I am a fool and misunderstood the situation. That's equally likely.</p>

							</div>

								
					
