<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>absolutely brilliant scope going on here!!! really sad it took me this long to get around reading all of them but easily one of the more entertaining things to come out of 2018, and definitely a concept i can go to sleep to at night for many nights to come</p>
<p>feels like qntm's Fine Structure in terms of the frisson it makes me feel, but a lot tighter (which isnt a high bar tbh) AND collaborated on over the span of like what two months??? which holy shit. things like this make me sad that this site is for free. imagine being this talented and getting paid in upvotes. ugh</p>
<p>if anything, i'm sad each introductory branch isn't more fully-explored - there's so much that can be done with grassroots-up investigations of the mystery that isn't shown, especially given how much world has been built around the Nobody/BQ/UIU-hegemony threads. i'd love to see the ways in which these unlikely heroes tap on their resources to strike back - and of course, how they end up crushed by the superior multiversal might of Mainline (or escape it?)</p>
<p>10/10, this should be so much more highly rated than it is now. a masterclass in scenario-building that conveys style, finesse, and affective impact. gib more pls</p>
<p>ed: ok decibelle is right, the blurb does NOT do this justice.</p>
</div>
</div>
